Today, I went to the park.
There, I saw a parrot.

It was sitting on a branch.
It was a free parrot—not in a cage.

Suddenly, we started talking.
We spent a nice morning together.

It told me about the sky.
I listened with a smile.

The sun was warm on my face.
Birds sang all around us.

Then the parrot spread its wings.
It flew to a taller tree.

I waved and said goodbye.
It was a morning I will never forget.
